###########################################################################
#  text_verbatim_whitespace - exercises z53.c's xml:space="preserve"      #
#  heuristic on a @Verbatim block whose source contains runs of internal  #
#  whitespace and leading indentation.  Without preserve, SVG renderers   #
#  collapse the runs to single spaces and visibly drop characters,        #
#  diverging from the PostScript reference.  With the heuristic active,   #
#  the SVG <text> element carries xml:space="preserve" so rsvg-convert   #
#  keeps the columns aligned, matching the fixed-width PS render.        #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A verbatim block exercising preserved whitespace and aligned columns:
@LP
@IndentedDisplay @F @Verbatim @Begin
key      value      note
foo      1          first
bar      22         second
baz      333        third
@End @Verbatim
@PP
Text resumes normally after the verbatim block.
@End @Text
